cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recovering 3D structures from 2D observations of the world. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it uses deep generative models and probabilistic inference to achieve its goals. The paper may also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with 3D structures and their representation. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it uses neural networks for inference.
